# React Component Standards

## Component Size & Complexity

**Soft limit: 200 lines per component.** Beyond this, evaluate if the component has multiple responsibilities.

**Hard split required when:**
- Component exceeds 300 lines **OR**
- Component handles 3+ distinct responsibilities

```typescript
// ❌ Wrong: 350 lines, handles auth + data fetching + UI + validation
export function UserDashboard() {
  const [user, setUser] = useState(null);
  const [posts, setPosts] = useState([]);
  const [isAuthenticated, setIsAuthenticated] = useState(false);
  // ... 340+ more lines
}

// ✅ Correct: Split into focused components
export function UserDashboard() {
  return (
    <AuthGuard>
      <UserProfile />
      <UserPosts />
    </AuthGuard>
  );
}
```

**Identify responsibilities by asking:**
1. Data fetching/management
2. User interaction handling
3. Layout/presentation
4. Business logic/validation

If a component does 3+, split it.

---

## Custom Hooks

**Extract custom hooks only when reused 2+ times.** Single use = keep logic inline within component.

```typescript
// ❌ Wrong: Premature extraction for single use
function useUserData(userId: string) {
  const [user, setUser] = useState(null);
  useEffect(() => {
    fetchUser(userId).then(setUser);
  }, [userId]);
  return user;
}

function UserProfile({ userId }: Props) {
  const user = useUserData(userId); // Only used here
}

// ✅ Correct: Keep inline for single use
function UserProfile({ userId }: Props) {
  const [user, setUser] = useState(null);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    fetchUser(userId).then(setUser);
  }, [userId]);
}

// ✅ Extract when used 2+ times
function UserProfile({ userId }: Props) {
  const user = useUserData(userId);
}

function UserSettings({ userId }: Props) {
  const user = useUserData(userId); // Second usage justifies extraction
}
```

**Create new hook file only if it reduces total lines by 20%+.**

```typescript
// Before extraction: 15 lines × 2 components = 30 total lines
// After extraction: 15 lines (hook) + 2 lines (call) × 2 = 19 total lines
// Reduction: 36% → Justified ✅

// Before extraction: 5 lines × 2 components = 10 total lines  
// After extraction: 5 lines (hook) + 2 lines (call) × 2 = 9 total lines
// Reduction: 10% → Keep inline ❌
```

