## Memoization

**Zero tolerance for premature memoization.** Use `useMemo` and `useCallback` only when:

1. **Measured performance issue** (React DevTools Profiler shows excessive renders) **OR**
2. **Obvious expensive computation** (complex calculations, large array processing)

```typescript
// ❌ Wrong: Premature optimization
function UserList({ users }: Props) {
  const sortedUsers = useMemo(
    () => users.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name)),
    [users]
  ); // Unnecessary - no evidence it's slow
  
  return <div>{sortedUsers.map(u => <UserCard key={u.id} user={u} />)}</div>;
}

// ✅ Correct: Direct computation
function UserList({ users }: Props) {
  const sortedUsers = users.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
  return <div>{sortedUsers.map(u => <UserCard key={u.id} user={u} />)}</div>;
}

// ✅ Valid useMemo: Expensive computation
function DataVisualization({ data }: Props) {
  const processedData = useMemo(() => {
    // Complex calculation over 10k+ items
    return data.map(item => ({
      ...item,
      computed: expensiveCalculation(item), // Proven slow
      aggregated: data.filter(d => d.category === item.category)
    }));
  }, [data]);
}

// ✅ Valid useCallback: Prevents child re-renders
const MemoizedChild = memo(Child);

function Parent() {
  const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
    // Stable reference prevents MemoizedChild re-render
  }, []);
  
  return <MemoizedChild onClick={handleClick} />;
}
```

**When to measure:**
- Component renders 10+ times per second
- User reports UI lag
- Profiler shows >16ms render time

**Prefer these alternatives first:**
1. Move expensive computation outside component
2. Use React Server Components
3. Virtualize long lists (react-window, react-virtualized)
4. Split component to isolate re-renders

